            ("5. CCPA SERVICE PROVIDER OBLIGATIONS", '5.1 To the extent Provider processes Personal Information subject to the CCPA, Provider is a "Service Provider" per Cal. Civ. Code Section 1798.140(ag).\n\n5.2 Provider certifies: (a) Provider shall not sell or share Personal Information as defined by the CCPA; (b) Provider shall not retain, use, or disclose Personal Information for any purpose other than performing the Services; (c) Provider shall not retain, use, or disclose Personal Information outside the direct business relationship between Provider and Client; (d) Provider shall not combine Personal Information with information from other sources except as permitted by Cal. Civ. Code Section 1798.140(e)(6) (security incident detection) and (e)(7) (service quality improvement for Client only).\n\n5.3 Provider shall assist Client in responding to verifiable consumer requests (know, access, delete, correct) within ten (10) business days and direct subprocessors to comply. Retention is permitted only under Cal. Civ. Code Section 1798.105(d).\n\n5.4 Provider shall notify Client within five (5) business days if it can no longer meet CCPA obligations. Client may take reasonable steps to remediate unauthorized use.\n\n5.5 Provider shall allow compliance audits not more than once per twelve (12) months.\n\n5.6 Upon termination, Provider shall delete all Personal Information within thirty (30) calendar days and certify deletion in writing.'),
